{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1784492973,"nonce":"M04csFryN8f9wK9fF1e9oOvZ3ms=","message":"Phase 3 PR 5 (PostgreSQL exclusion constraints) MERGED — PR #115, squash a7d72a7. Adds ExclusionModel {name, method, elements, predicate, deferrability} on TableModel.exclusions with a per-element ExclusionElement {term: Column or Expression, operator, operator_class, collation, direction, nulls}, threaded through the full object template (IR, capabilities, diff/plan Add/Drop/AlterExclusion, KDL, PG render + introspect, MySQL/SQLite reject, CLI). PG render: inline CONSTRAINT ... EXCLUDE ... in CREATE TABLE + ALTER TABLE ADD CONSTRAINT incrementally; dropped as a constraint; altered as drop+add. PG introspect: pg_constraint contype x joined to the backing index for the per-element facts, conexclop to pg_operator for operators, condeferrable/condeferred for deferrability; reads only the index key columns (a covering INCLUDE column is not an element); default sort order and non-deferrable fold to None so a squealy-authored exclusion replans empty. An exclusion owns a pg_class index, so it claims a distinct ObjectKind::Exclusion and an exclusion vs same-name index/UNIQUE/PK swap is rejected at plan time. Contract: a scalar-and-range squealy-authored exclusion (multi-element, operator classes, partial predicate, deferrable) publish then introspect then replan-empty, live-tested on PG with btree_gist. codex 2 rounds; the one clear bug (INCLUDE fabricating a keyless element) fixed with a disable-to-fail live test, the bounded index-backed swap rejected, seven niche/pre-existing edges deferred with maintainer sign-off and filed as follow-up d7c71e4 (same-name check/FK swap + cross-table move; cross-schema operator + explicit-default-opclass fidelity; INCLUDE modeling; and two pre-existing column co-operation ordering edges shared with the existing index handling). Epic STAYS OPEN. Phase 3 progress: PR 1